    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-07-09T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-07-09T09:00:00-05:00" n="402"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d402">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">384.11/173: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-07-09T17:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 9, 1936—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 12—9:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>463. Department’s 299, July 7, 8 p.m. There are at present 12 American men, 11
                    women and 10 children in territory of Ethiopia which has not yet been occupied
                    by the Italians. Of these only five have been heard from since May 1st (see my
                    449, July 1, noon<note n="85" xml:id="d402fn85">Not printed.</note>). The others
                    have evidently been unable to get runners through and my attempts have also been
                    in vain. Situation essentially as anticipated in last paragraph of my 350, May
                    17, 9 a.m.<note n="86" xml:id="d402fn86">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_76">p. 76</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Other questions in Department’s 299 will be answered in subsequent telegrams.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
